Use the standard library
This is how to largest_prime_factor of n:
   Remember that x is n
   Remember that largest is 1
   Do this while remainder of x and 2 is 0:
      Remember that largest is 2
      Remember that x is quotient of x and 2
   End do
   Remember that f is 3
   Do this while product of f and f is at most x:
      Do this while remainder of x and f is 0:
         Remember that largest is f
         Remember that x is quotient of x and f
      End do
      Remember that f is sum of f and 2
   End do
   When x is more than 1, then:
      Remember that largest is x
   End when
   The answer is largest
Now you know
>>> largest_prime_factor of 13195
29
>>> largest_prime_factor of 2048
2
>>> largest_prime_factor of 15
5